params.message: You will need 1 ethanol wells in the deepwell plate all with 10mL each, starting at A7, B2.
You will need 114.99999999999999 of strep beads in column 1 of the deepwell reagent plate on deck, B2.
You will need 229.99999999999997 of fast binding buffer in columns A2, A3, A4, A5 of the deepwell reagent plate on deck, B2.
You will need water in A6 of the deepwell reagent plate on deck, B2.
You will need 103.49999999999999 of purification beads in column A7 of the deepwell reagent plate on deck, B2.
You will need 229.99999999999997 of wash buffer 1 in columns 1 and 2 of the deepwell reagent plate on temperature module, D1
You will need 229.99999999999997 of wash buffer 2 in columns 3, 4, 5 of the deepwell reagent plate on temperature module, D1
You will need 2.875 of primer in column 1 of the pcr plate on cold aluminum block, A2
You will need 28.749999999999996 of amp mix in column 2 of the pcr plate on cold aluminum block, A2
Combine sample and strep beads for 16 hour hybridization. Place back on slot C2

Water added. Store 22.5ul in freezer. Protocol continues with remaining 22.5ul in armadillo plate in D2.
             Load the cold aluminum block with armadillo plate on slot A2, with 2.875ul of ilmn amplification primers in the first column,
             and 28.749999999999996ul of equinox library amp mix in column 2 of the cold aluminum block.
Primers and amp mix added. Plate on slot 2 ready for PCR according to section 2.4.
